sec.p:
All calculations have been performed by using the Vienna ab initio simulation package (VASP)15–17. Structure optimization have been performed based on the generalized gradient approximation (GGA) within Perdew–Burke–Ernzerhof (PBE) parameterization18,19. The Monkhorst–Pack scheme with 9 × 9 × 1 k-point grid was used for the integration in the first Brillouin zone. The lattice parameters and ionic positions were fully relaxed until the total energies and forces were less than 10−5 eV and 0.01 eVÅ−1, respectively. The DFT-D2 method of Grimme20 was used to describe the weak dispersion forces. The vacuum space spanning was set to 40 Å in the z direction. For electronic structures calculation, a 13 × 13 × 1 Monkhorst–Pack mesh was used for both the DOS and band structure. Since PBE functional often underestimates the bandgaps, we have also calculated the band gaps at the HSE0621 level for comparison. Optical properties can be described by the dielectric function:εω=ε1ω+iε2ω\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
